frameDefinitions: A Communicator (whose Location may be indicated) directs a Communication to an Addressee at a particular Address.
This frame concerns Communicators communicating with each other with the aid of a Means of communication such as a telephone.
In this frame an Informer informs the Authorities of the illegal or otherwise improper Behavior of the Wrongdoer. '
An Author creates a Text, either written, such as a letter, or spoken, such as a speech,  that contains meaningful linguistic tokens, and may have a particular Addressee in mind.
The absolute Value of a quantifiable Attribute  of an item is determined by adding up the values for the Attribute of the individuals or parts that make up the item.
frameExamples: Disgruntled voters <t>phoned</t> Congressman Neil at his Washington residence with complaints about the recent increases in corporate welfare.
Tony <t>reported</t> Michael to the police for breaking into his car.
I <t>penned</t> a letter concerning racism to Congress.
Defence is provided in West Germany by armed forces whose number <t>totals</t> close to half a million men and women
listRoleDefinitions: The person who uses language in the written or spoken modality to convey a message to another person.
The person that receives the message from the <fen>Communicator</fen>.
This role is used for a (metaphorical) place in a system of communication where <fen>Communicator</fen>s and <fen>Addressee</fen>s can access the system.

The information that the <fen>Communicator</fen> wishes to impart to the <fen>Addressee</fen>, often to get a particular response. In this frame the <fen>Communication</fen> is not necessarily received by the <fen>Addressee</fen>.
This is the subject matter to which the message pertains. It is typically expressed as a PP Complement headed by 'about'.
This role identifies the time when the Agent acts intentionally.
This role identifies the place where the intentional act occurs.

This role is the person who uses the <fen>Means</fen> of communication to deliver the <fen>Message</fen> to the Addressee. The Speaker is normally expressed as the External Argument of target verbs, or as the Genitive modifier of  nouns.

<fen>Addressee</fen> is the person to whom the <fen>Message</fen> is communicated. When this role is expressed, it often appears in a prepositional phrase introduced by to, or as the direct object, or as the first object in a double object construction.
This role identifies the content that the <fen>Communicator</fen> communicates to the <fen>Addressee</fen>. It can be expressed as a clause or as a noun phrase.
<fen>Topic</fen> is the subject matter to which the <fen>Message</fen> pertains. It is typically expressed as a PP Complement headed by about.

This Frame Element refers to the Instrument of Communication that is used by the <fen>Communicator</fen> (and <fen>Addressee</fen>). Each LU in this frame incorporates the <fen>Means</fen> frame element.
The <fen>Informer</fen> reports the activities of the <fen>Wrongdoer</fen> to the <fen>Authorities</fen>.
The <fen>Wrongdoer</fen> has his or her activities reported to the <fen>Authorities</fen>.
The <fen>Authorities</fen> are the officials, government or otherwise, who handle misbehavior.
The <fen>Behavior</fen> is the action or actions for which the <fen>Wrongdoer</fen> is reported.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Informer</fen> reports the <fen>Behavior</fen> of the <fen>Wrongdoer</fen>.
The <fen>Place</fen> is the location where the reporting occurs.
The <fen>Author</fen> produces a particular <fen>Text</fen>.
The entity which results from the act of writing or speaking.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> at which the text is created.
Where the event takes place.
The value of an attribute.
The scalar property of a concrete or abstract entity.
A set of numbers that add up to the <fen>Value</fen>.
listRoleExamples: The company must be able to call <fex> potential customers</fex>.
<fex>The President</fex> cabled his assistant to cancel all of his appointments.
The President cabled <fex>his assistant</fex> to cancel all other engagements.
During the first three years of drug squad work, <fex>arrests</fex> totaled some sixty-four persons.
Look, you turn those into numbers, and then <fex>592 and 74</fex> total 666, right?
